If you want to replace the blank spaces with *, you need to specify a fill character in the format.

🔹 Syntax:
{:fill align width}

👉 fill = character to fill (like *)
👉 align = < left, > right, ^ center

✅ Modified Code (Using * instead of space)
name = "Ram"

print("{:*<10}".format(name))   # Left align
print("{:*>10}".format(name))   # Right align
print("{:*^10}".format(name))   # Center align
✅ Output
Ram*******
*******Ram
***Ram****
🎯 Explanation
Format	Meaning
:*<10	Fill *, left align, width 10
:*>10	Fill *, right align, width 10
:*^10	Fill *, center align, width 10
✅ Using f-string (Modern Way ✔)
