To fill * instead of blank space in:

print("{:10}".format(name))

you must add the fill character + alignment symbol.

✅ Correct Format
print("{:*<10}".format(name))
🔹 Example
name = "Ram"

print("{:*<10}".format(name))   # Left align
print("{:*>10}".format(name))   # Right align
print("{:*^10}".format(name))   # Center align
🔹 Output
Ram*******
*******Ram
***Ram****
🎯 Rule
{:fill alignment width}

* → fill character

< → left

> → right

^ → center

10 → total width

If you write only:

print("{:10}".format(name))

👉 Default fill character = space